  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"Stand Up India\" in the scheme \"Stand Up India, Start Up India\"?",
  "response": "\"Stand Up India\" is a scheme launched by the Government of India in 2016, primarily aimed at promoting entrepreneurship among Scheduled Castes (SC), Scheduled Tribes (ST), and Women entrepreneurs. The key objectives of the scheme are:\n\n1. To provide financial assistance to marginalized sections of society\n2. To encourage first-generation entrepreneurs from SC/ST and women categories\n3. To help them start greenfield enterprises in manufacturing, services, or trading sectors\n4. To provide bank loans ranging from \u20b910 lakh to \u20b91 crore\n5. To support individual loans for setting up new businesses\n6. To promote financial inclusion and economic empowerment\n\nThe scheme complements the \"Start Up India\" initiative, which focuses on creating a supportive ecosystem for innovative startups across India. While \"Start Up India\" is broader and targets all entrepreneurs, \"Stand Up India\" specifically focuses on supporting marginalized sections of society by providing them with financial and institutional support to start their own enterprises.\n\nThe goal is to foster entrepreneurship, create employment opportunities, and promote economic growth among traditionally underrepresented groups in the Indian economy.",
